values:
I don't know quite how to work through my fear of LJ, so I bid you guys a goodbye on this journal...unless of course, I conquer the confusion that I face...

Hasta Pasta, much love in the hood.

(Moons

I'm at the library and its 5:12pm on a Friday! I have no idea why I'm here other than I wanted to be somewhere else other than my room! Is that rediculous? Probably...maybe I will hit up bored.com and pass some more time. I wonder whats really going on with me?!

Hasta.

Ah I've only had my first two days but i am already feeling overwhelmed!  good news is i am in this amazing student outdoor leadership class that i'm very very excited about :) good fun learning to be a leader! 

April i miss you in math. the other april does too, and same with the loud annoying girl. :) love you.

I'm watching festival express. 
feeling super electronically savvy this morning because i have my cell phone charging, i'm typing on my laptop while watching the TV, and I have my iPod hooked up to edit what the fuck is on it!

Sheesh I'm so awesome....or something.

anyways, Christmas was less than exciting.  I always get stuff I won't ever use in like 50 years, so I just give it away to my family. I ended up with a harness and shoes (god bless my mother) an iPod (yay for dad) and some warm socks (alright aunt carol!) ;-)

peace in the middle east!

*moons

WELCOME to my very first entry. i have NO fucking clue how to use live journal....HELP!

;-)

peace and love.

Moons
